summary.name: Bird Strikes
summary.dataset_description: A dataset containing information about bird strikes incidents involving aircrafts.

properties.description: Name of the airport where the bird strike occurred.
Make and model of the aircraft involved in the bird strike.
Amount of damage caused to the aircraft due to the bird strike.
Date of the flight when the bird strike occurred.
Airline operator of the aircraft involved in the bird strike.
State of origin of the flight.
Phase of flight during which the bird strike occurred.
Size of the wildlife involved in the bird strike.
Species of the wildlife involved in the bird strike.
Time of day when the bird strike occurred.
Other costs associated with the bird strike incident.
Cost of repairing the aircraft after the bird strike.
Total cost of the bird strike incident.
Indicated airspeed of the aircraft in knots at the time of the bird strike.

goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by airport?
goals.visualization: bar chart of number of bird strikes per airport
goals.rationale: This helps identify airports with high bird strike incidents and can inform decisions on bird control measures.

goals.question: What is the most common aircraft make and model involved in bird strikes?
goals.visualization: horizontal bar chart of count of bird strikes by aircraft make and model
goals.rationale: This information can be used to inform aircraft manufacturers and operators on potential design improvements to reduce bird strike incidents.

goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by wildlife species?
goals.visualization: pie chart of percentage of bird strikes by wildlife species
goals.rationale: This helps identify the most common wildlife species involved in bird strikes and can inform decisions on wildlife management strategies.

goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by phase of flight?
goals.visualization: stacked bar chart of count of bird strikes by phase of flight and time of day
goals.rationale: This helps identify the phases of flight with the highest bird strike incidents and can inform decisions on flight scheduling and bird control measures.

goals.question: What is the relationship between aircraft speed and amount of damage caused by bird strikes?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of aircraft speed (x-axis) and amount of damage (y-axis)
goals.rationale: This helps identify if there is a correlation between aircraft speed and amount of damage caused by bird strikes, which can inform decisions on flight speed limits and aircraft design improvements.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Group by Airport_Name and count bird strikes
    bird_strikes_by_airport = data.groupby('Airport_Name').size().reset_index(name='count')

    # Sort by count in descending order
    bird_strikes_by_airport = bird_strikes_by_airport.sort_values('count', ascending=False)

    # Create bar chart
    plt.bar(bird_strikes_by_airport['Airport_Name'], bird_strikes_by_airport['count'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('Airport Name')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Bird Strikes')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of bird strikes by airport?', wrap=True)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    aircraft_counts = data['Aircraft_Make_Model'].value_counts()
    aircraft_counts = aircraft_counts.head(10)
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.barh(aircraft_counts.index, aircraft_counts.values, color='tab:blue')
    plt.xlabel('Number of Bird Strikes')
    plt.ylabel('Aircraft Make and Model')
    plt.title('What is the most common aircraft make and model involved in bird strikes?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Bird Strikes'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    species_counts = data['Wildlife_Species'].value_counts()
    species_counts.plot.pie(autopct='%.2f%%', figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.title("What is the distribution of bird strikes by wildlife species?", wrap=True)
    plt.ylabel("")

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Flight_Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Flight_Date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Flight_Date'])]
    
    phase_time_counts = data.groupby(['Phase_of_flight', 'Time_of_day']).size().unstack()
    phase_time_counts.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    
    plt.title("What is the distribution of bird strikes by phase of flight?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Phase of Flight")
    plt.ylabel("Count of Bird Strikes")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title="Time of Day")
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Flight_Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Flight_Date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Flight_Date'])]
    
    damage_order = ['None', 'Minor', 'Medium', 'Substantial', 'Destroyed']
    data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'] = pd.Categorical(data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'], categories=damage_order, ordered=True)
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['Speed_IAS_in_knots'], data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'], c=data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'].cat.codes, cmap='viridis')
    
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Amount of Damage")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    
    plt.xlabel('Aircraft Speed (knots)')
    plt.ylabel('Amount of Damage')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between aircraft speed and amount of damage caused by bird strikes?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
